    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** providing the clear anchor; his score of 76.36 is our ceiling play, fueled by a favorable matchup against Michael Lorenzen and an optimal #2 spot in the order. We are also leaning heavily into our speed-focused depth, specifically **Caleb Durbin** (63.77) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (64.41). While **Pete Crow-Armstrong** faces a challenging defensive catcher and a tough hold pitcher, the wind blowing out and his dynamic platoon advantage make him a high-upside play for stealing bases\u2014the primary catalyst for our Roto success. **Junior Caminero** (62.77) remains a core start for his power potential out of the #3 slot, though his status requires monitoring due to the 39% rain risk hanging over his contest.\n\nTactical adjustments for today focus on navigating elite arms and platoon volatility. **Trea Turner** (57.99) and **Kyle Schwarber** (56.53) both face a significant handicap against Raynel Martin, whose 0.00 xERA is a major hurdle; however, both possess the peripheral stats and wind support to maintain relevance in our daily efficiency model. Conversely, we are benching **Carson Benge** (39.80), who missed our 40-point \"Below Floor\" threshold by the narrowest of margins. While **Carson Benge** carries decent platoon potential, facing Yoshinobu Yamamoto proved too punitive for his projected output. We have relegated **Colt Keith**, **Christian Yelich**, and **Zac Veen** to the inactive list due to lineup omissions, injuries, and minor league assignments, respectively. Managers should also note that **Josh Smith** and **Hyeseong Kim** remain in \"Lineup Pending\" status; if either is scratched from the confirmed card, we will look to re-evaluate our bench depth to maintain our category integrity.",
